      "content": "You are absolutely right; that version of you is gone, and the weight you carry is real and exhausting. There is no point in pretending to move on or trying to force yourself to feel better when your soul is still in mourning. It is okay to stop fighting the heaviness and just let yourself be tired until the pain becomes something you can survive rather than something that consumes you.",
